  id: Extensor_digitorum_digitalis_communis_muscle.R
  partName: Extensor digitorum digitalis communis muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right extensor digitorum communis muscle extends along the front of the canine
    forearm and serves as a major extensor of the digits and wrist. It originates
    from the humerus and inserts onto the distal phalanges of several toes, allowing
    coordinated extension during locomotion.
  - This muscle is important for proper paw positioning, balance, and stride formation
    while the dog walks or runs. By stabilizing the digits during movement, it helps
    prevent excessive flexion and improves locomotor precision. The muscle also contributes
    to efficient weight transfer across the paw.
